list.name: Part
list.description: This map object represents a part within the map.

members.name: Name
members.description: The name of this entry.

members.name: Model Name
members.description: The model used by this part; requires an entry in ModelParam.

members.name: Instance ID
members.description: Involved with serialization.

members.name: Layout Path
members.description: A path to a .sib file, presumably some kind of editor placeholder.

members.name: Position
members.description: The position of this part.

members.name: Rotation
members.description: The rotation of this part.

members.name: Scale
members.description: The scale of this part. Scale will NOT affect the scale of enemies or the scale of in-built collision for objects and assets (except for assets in Elden Ring).

members.name: Game Edition Disable Type
members.description: Toggles the loading of this part.

members.name: Entity ID
members.description: Identifies the part in event scripts.

members.name: Uses Parts Draw Param ID
members.description: Enables use of PartsDrawParamID. If false, asset param is used instead.

members.name: Parts Draw Param ID
members.description: The Parts Draw Param ID to use.

members.name: Is Point Light Shadow Source
members.description: Is this part to be considered a Point Light shadow source.

members.name: Is Shadow Source
members.description: Is this part to be considered a shadow source.

members.name: Is Static Shadow Source
members.description: Is this part to be considered a static shadow source.

members.name: Is Cascade Shadow Source
members.description: Is this part to be considered a cascade shadow source.

members.name: Is Shadow Destination
members.description: Is this part to be considered a shadow destination.

members.name: Is Shadow Only
members.description: Is this part only rendered when calculating the shadow pass.

members.name: Is Drawn by Reflection Camera
members.description: Is this part drawn by the reflection camera.

members.name: Is Drawn Only by the Reflection Camera
members.description: Is this part only drawn within the reflection camera.

members.name: Entity Group ID
members.description: A entity group ID associated with this part. Allows multiple parts to be identified with a single entity ID.

members.name: Display Group
members.description: A display group for this part.

members.name: Draw Group
members.description: A draw group for this part.

members.name: Collision Mask
members.description: A collision mask for this part.

members.name: Display Group
members.description: A display group for this part.

members.name: Light Set ID
members.description: ID of the value set from LightSet ParamEditor to use.

members.name: Fog Param ID
members.description: ID of the value set from FogParamEditor to use.

members.name: Light Scattering ID
members.description: ID of the value set from LightScattering : ParamEditor to use.

members.name: Environment Map ID
members.description: ID of the value set from Env Map:Editor to use.

members.name: Transition Time
members.description: Transition time between scenes.

members.name: Graphics Param Override: [1]
members.description: Value of the hundredths place of a Gparam to override use.

members.name: Graphics Param Override: [2]
members.description: Value of the hundredths place of a Gparam to override [1] with.

members.name: Graphics Param Override: [3]
members.description: Value of the hundredths place of a Gparam to override [1] and [2] with.

members.name: Graphics Param Override: [4]
members.description: Value of the hundredths place of a Gparam to override [1], [2] and [3] with.

members.name: Map ID
members.description: The four ID parts of the map that this map object belongs to. Used in overworld map tiles to link the map object to a specific overworld tile. Order is reverse of map ID string.

members.name: Grass Type Param: [0]
members.description: The grass type param to use with this asset.

members.name: Grass Type Param: [1]
members.description: The grass type param to use with this asset.

members.name: Grass Type Param: [2]
members.description: The grass type param to use with this asset.

members.name: Grass Type Param: [3]
members.description: The grass type param to use with this asset.

members.name: Grass Type Param: [4]
members.description: The grass type param to use with this asset.

members.name: Grass Type Param: [5]
members.description: The grass type param to use with this asset.

list.name: Enemy
list.description: This map object represents an in-game entity, used for enemies, characters and interaction points that make use of the Talk system.

members.name: Think Param ID
members.description: An ID in NPCThinkParam that determines the enemy's AI characteristics.

members.name: NPC Param ID
members.description: An ID in NPCParam that determines a variety of enemy properties.

members.name: Talk ID
members.description: An ID pointing to an .ESD file that contains the a Talk setup.

members.name: Platoon ID
members.description: An ID pointing to a platoon type, used by patrolling groups of enemies.

members.name: Character Init ID
members.description: An ID in CharaInitParam that determines a human's inventory and stats.

members.name: Collision Part Name
members.description: The Name of the collision that this Enemy starts on.

members.name: Walk Route Name
members.description: Walk route followed by this enemy.

members.name: Activation Condition ID
members.description: ID in ChrActivateConditionParam that affects enemy appearance conditions.

members.name: Backup Event Anim ID
members.description: Default event animation to apply to the enemy whilst it is idle.

members.name: SpEffect Set ID
members.description: Refers to SpEffectSetParam ID. Applies SpEffects to an enemy.

list.name: Collision
list.description: This map object represents a form of collision. Typically used to block player or enemy movement, but also used for detection such as for kill planes, or the generation of special footstep visual effects, such as in water or lava.

members.name: Hit Filter ID
members.description: Sets collision behavior. Fall collision, death collision, enemy-only collision, etc.

members.name: Play Region ID
members.description: Used to determine invasion eligibility.

members.name: Disable Torrent
members.description: Disable being able to summon/ride Torrent.

members.name: Fast Travel Enabled Flag
members.description: Disables Fast Travel if Event Flag is not set.

list.name: ConnectCollision
list.description: This map object represents a form of collision used to connect different maps together. When the player steps on a ConnectCollision, the specified map(s) will be loaded.

members.name: Collision Name
members.description: The collision part to attach to.

members.name: Map ID
members.description: The map to load when on this collision.

list.name: Asset
list.description: This map object represents an in-game object of varying sizes, from clutter to cliffs. Supports in-built collision, however not all assets use it.

members.name: Asset SFX Param Relative ID
members.description: Value added onto model ID determining AssetModelSfxParam to use.

members.name: Disable Torrent
members.description: Disable being able to summon/ride Torrent, but only when asset isn't referencing collision DisableTorrent.

members.name: Disable upon Map Load - Map ID
members.description: Disables the asset when the specified map is loaded.

list.name: Player
list.description: This map object represents a player point, which is used to place the player when warping between maps, or on map reset.

list.name: Map Piece
list.description: This map object represents a map piece, which is used to form the base structure of a map.

list.name: Dummy Asset
list.description: This map object represents a dummied-out form of an Asset.

list.name: Dummy Enemy
list.description: This map object represents a dummied-out form of an Enemy.

list.name: Event
list.description: This map object represents an event within the map.

members.name: Entity ID
members.description: Identifies the Event in event scripts.

list.name: Treasure
list.description: This map object is used to configure an item pick-up, defining a relationshop between an asset and an itemlot.

members.name: Attached Part Name
members.description: The part that the treasure is attached to.

members.name: Item Lot ID
members.description: The item lot to be given.

members.name: Action Button ID
members.description: If not -1, uses an entry from ActionButtonParam for the pickup prompt.

members.name: Pickup Anim ID
members.description: Animation to play when taking this treasure.

members.name: Is in Chest
members.description: Changes the text of the pickup prompt.

members.name: Starts Disabled
members.description: Whether the treasure should be hidden by default.

list.name: Generator
list.description: This map object is used to configure a generator, which is a group of attributes that determine the respawn state of a set of linked Enemies at a set of linked SpawnPoints.

members.name: Maximum Generated Count
members.description: The maximum number of enemies that this generator can generate in total.

members.name: Generator Type
members.description: The spawn location behavior to use upon a generation interval.

members.name: Maximum Spawn Count
members.description: The maximum number of enemies that this generator can generate upon a generation interval.

members.name: Random Spawn Count: Minimum
members.description: The minimum number to use when determining the amount of enemies to generate within a generation interval.

members.name: Random Spawn Count: Maximum
members.description: The maximum number to use when determining the amount of enemies to generate within a generation interval.

members.name: Generation Interval: Minimum
members.description: The minimum time interval (in seconds) between each generation interval.

members.name: Generation Interval: Maximum
members.description: The maximum time interval (in seconds) between each generation interval.

members.name: Initial Spawn Count
members.description: The initial number of enemies to spawn upon initialization of the generator.

members.name: Spawn Region Names
members.description: Regions where parts will spawn from.

members.name: Spawn Part Names
members.description: Parts that will be respawned.

list.name: Obj Act
list.description: This map object is used to configure the interaction state of an Asset.

members.name: ObjAct Part Name
members.description: The part to be interacted with.

members.name: ObjAct ID
members.description: A row in ObjActParam.

list.name: Navmesh
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Pseudo Multiplayer
list.description: This map object is used to configure a NPC Enemy that emulates the online invasion mechanic.

members.name: Host Entity ID
members.description: The NPC whose world you're entering.

members.name: Event Flag ID
members.description: Set when inside the event's region, unset when outside it.

members.name: Activation Goods ID
members.description: ID of a goods item that is used to trigger the event.

list.name: PlatoonInfo
list.description: This map object is used to configure a set of enemies into a platoon group, which can take on specific formations and speeds.

members.name: Platoon Script ID
members.description: The platoon script to apply when activated.

members.name: Group Part Names
members.description: The parts that belong to this platoon.

list.name: PatrolInfo
list.description: This map object is used to configure a set of enemies into a patrol group, which will follow a set of patrol nodes.

members.name: Patrol Type
members.description: Determines patrol behavior. 0 = return to first region on loop, 1 = go through list backwards on loop, etc.

members.name: Walk Region Names
members.description: The regions that belong to this patrol.

list.name: Mount
list.description: This map object is used to define the association between two Enemies, allowing one to mount the other as a horse.

members.name: Rider Part Name
members.description: The rider Part that may ride the mount Part.

members.name: Mount Part Name
members.description: The mount Part.

list.name: Sign Pool
list.description: This map object is used to define the association between an Asset and a Summoning Pool region.

members.name: Sign Part Name
members.description: The Part that the signpool is associated with.

members.name: Sign Puddle Param ID
members.description: The ID of the SignPuddleParam row to use for this signpool.

list.name: Retry Point
list.description: This map object is used to define a Stake of Marika.

members.name: Retry Part Name
members.description: The Part that is associated with this retry point.

members.name: Trigger Event Flag ID
members.description: Flag that must be set for retry point to be available.

members.name: Retry Distance
members.description: The distance at which the retry point is active (only used if no retry region is set).

members.name: Retry Region Name
members.description: The Region that this retry point covers.

list.name: Region
list.description: This map object represents a region within the map.

members.name: Shape
members.description: The shape of the region.

members.name: Position
members.description: The location of the region.

members.name: Rotation
members.description: The rotiation of the region, in degrees.

members.name: Map Studio Layer
members.description: Controls whether the region is active in different ceremonies.

members.name: Activation Part Name
members.description: If specified, the region is only active when the part is loaded.

members.name: Entity ID
members.description: Identifies the region in event scripts.

list.name: Auto Draw Group Point
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Buddy Summon Point
list.description: This map object was part of a prototype Buddy Summon implementation, but is no longer used.

list.name: Connection
list.description: This map object is used to define the positional offset of another map in relation to the current map.

members.name: Target Map ID
members.description: Map ID this connection targets.

list.name: Dummy
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Environment Map Effect Box
list.description: This map object is used to define the Global Illumination configuration for a specific region.

members.name: Display Distance
members.description: Distance from camera required before enabling envmap. 0 = always enabled.

members.name: Fade Distance
members.description: Distance it takes for an envmap to fully transition into view.

members.name: Ambient Diffuse Intensity
members.description: Strength of ambient diffuse light.

members.name: Ambient Specular Intensity
members.description: Strength of ambient specular light.

members.name: Modify Light
members.description: Affects lighting with other fields when true. Possibly normalizes light when false.

list.name: Environment Map Point
list.description: This map object is used to define the Global Illumination configuration.

list.name: Environment Map Output
list.description: This map object is used to define the Global Illumination configuration.

list.name: Fall Prevention Removal
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Fast Travel Restriction
list.description: This map object is used to define a region where fast travel via the player's map is disabled.

members.name: Event Flag ID
members.description: Disables fast travel when flag is OFF.

list.name: Group Defeat Reward
list.description: This map object is used to configure a group that rewards the player flasks after all of the group members are dead.

members.name: Part Names
members.description: References to enemies to defeat to receive the reward.

list.name: Horse Ride Override
list.description: This map object is used to configure a region where the player's ability to ride Torrent is either enabled or disabled, ignoring the collision or asset's flag for this.

members.name: Override Type
members.description: 1 = Forbid riding torrent, 2 = Permit riding torrent

list.name: Hitset
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Invasion Point
list.description: This map object is used to configure points where an invader may appear.

members.name: Selection Priority
members.description: The priority this point has over others during the selection process.

list.name: Map Point
list.description: This map object is used to define a map point that appears on the player's map.

members.name: World Map Point ID
members.description: Determines which WorldMapPointParam to use.

list.name: Map Point Discovery Override
list.description: This map object is used to configure a region that overrides the default parameters for discovering a specified map point.

list.name: Map Point Participation Override
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Map Name Override
list.description: This map object is used to configure a region where the area name prompt is replaced with another name.

members.name: Text ID
members.description: The FMG ID of the Location Name to show. Ignores the negative sign during lookup.

list.name: Message
list.description: This map object is used to configure a point where a pre-defined message should appear, and the contents of the message.

members.name: Message ID
members.description: ID of this message's text in the FMGs.

members.name: Is Hidden
members.description: Whether the message requires Seek Guidance to appear.

members.name: Message SFX ID
members.description: The FFX ID to use to display the message.

members.name: Enable Event Flag ID
members.description: Event Flag required to be ON for the message to appear.

members.name: Character Model Name
members.description: ID of character to render along with the message.

members.name: NPC Param ID
members.description: NpcParam ID to use when rendering a character with the message.

members.name: Animation ID
members.description: Animation ID to use when rendering a character with the message.

members.name: Character Init ID
members.description: CharaInitParam ID to use when rendering a character with the message.

list.name: Mount Jump
list.description: This map object is used to define a region where a Spiritspring is located.

members.name: Jump Height
members.description: Height the player will move upwards when activating the spiritspring.

list.name: Mount Jump Fall
list.description: This map object is used to define a region where a Spiritspring landing may occur. This type of landing prevents all fall damage.

list.name: Muffling Box
list.description: This map object is used to define a region where environmental sound is muffled in accordance with the specified parameters.

list.name: Muffling Plane
list.description: This map object is used to define a flat region where environmental sound is muffled in accordance with the specified parameters.

list.name: Muffling Portal
list.description: This map object is used to define a region where environmental sound is muffled in accordance with the specified parameters.

list.name: Navmesh Cutting
list.description: This map object is used to define a region where the navigation mesh can be 'cut'.

list.name: NPC Area
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Other
list.description: This map object is used to define a 'trigger' region used for various forms of detection and placement.

list.name: Patrol Route
list.description: This map object is used to define a patrol point that is used within a Patrol Info map object.

list.name: Play Area
list.description: This map object is used to define an area used to setup a Play Region within a map. Play Regions control various multiplayer parameters.

list.name: SFX
list.description: This map object is used to define a SFX that appears within a map.

members.name: Effect ID
members.description: The ID of the particle effect FFX.

members.name: Start Disabled
members.description: If true, the effect is off by default until enabled by an event script.

list.name: Sound
list.description: This map object is used to define a Sound that occurs within a map.

members.name: Sound Type
members.description: The category of the sound.

members.name: Sound ID
members.description: The ID of the sound.

members.name: Child Region Names
members.description: References to other regions used to build a composite shape.

list.name: Sound Region
list.description: This map object is used to define a region within a map that emits sound.

list.name: Spawn Point
list.description: This map object is used to define a point that is used for player respawning.

list.name: Weather Create Asset Point
list.description: Unknown.

list.name: Weather Override
list.description: This map object is used to define a region that overrides the default weather for the map.

members.name: Weather Lot ID
members.description: Determines which WeatherLotParam ID to use.

list.name: Wind Area
list.description: This map object is used to define a region that applies wind physics to any cloth-enabled models.

list.name: Wind SFX
list.description: This map object is used to define a region that displays wind visuals.

members.name: Effect ID
members.description: ID of the effect FFX.

members.name: Wind Area Name
members.description: Reference to a WindArea region.

list.name: Light
list.description: This map object represents a light emitter within a map.

members.name: Name
members.description: The name of this light.

members.name: Type
members.description:
The type of light.
Point: omnidirectional light.
Spot: cone of light.
Directional: light at a constant angle.

members.name: Diffuse Color
members.description: Color of the light on diffuse surfaces.

members.name: Diffuse Intensity
members.description: Intensity of diffuse lighting.

members.name: Specular Color
members.description: Color of the light on reflective surfaces.

members.name: Cast Shadows
members.description: Whether the light casts shadows.

members.name: Specular Intensity
members.description: Intensity of specular lighting.

members.name: Spot Light: Cone Angle
members.description: Tightness of the spot light beam. Only affects Spot lights.

members.name: Position
members.description: Center of the light.

members.name: Rotation
members.description: Rotation of a spot light.

members.name: Radius
members.description: Distance the light shines.

members.name: ShadowColor
members.description: Color of shadows cast by the light; alpha is relative to 100.

members.name: Flicker Interval: Minimum
members.description: Minimum time between flickers.

members.name: Flicker Interval: Maximum
members.description: Maximum time between flickers.

members.name: Flicker Brightness Multiplier
members.description: Multiplies the brightness of the light while flickering.

members.name: Event ID
members.description: Referenced by map events. Only used in DS2.

members.name: Spot Light: Near Clip
members.description: Distance at which spot light beam starts.

members.name: Spot Light: Width
members.description: Stretches the spot light beam.

members.name: Light Start Cutoff
members.description: Distance from start before light appears.

members.name: Enable State
members.description: Affects if a light appears normally, but details are unknown.

members.name: Enable Distance
members.description: Distance required for a light to transition into view. 0 = always enabled.
